We estimate standard errors of all parameters from the observed Fisher’s information, based on the “fast model”. It is known from the likelihood optimization theory that the observed Fisher’s information may not be suitable for a parameter near its boundary, which is applicable to the mixture weights π1, π2, π12, and the correlation of effect sizes ρ12. To mitigate this problem, we apply transformations— MATLAB’s logit() for π1, π2, π12, exp() for \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
